<subSubSection pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1437,1492,2023]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,420,1492,1518]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<typeStatus box="[151,269,1492,1518]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Lectotype</typeStatus>
designation.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Gussakovskij, V. V." box="[426,658,1492,1519]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 453" refId="ref73348" refString="Gussakovskij, V. V. (1935) Insectes Hymenopteres, Chalastogastra 1. In: Fauna SSSR. 2 (1). Moskva, Leningrad, pp. 1 - 453. [in Russian and German]" type="book chapter" year="1935">Gussakovskij (1935)</bibRefCitation>
examined only 
<specimenCount box="[836,989,1492,1519]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="generic">one specimen</specimenCount>
in Eversmann’s material (“Mir liegt nur das typische Stück von Eversmann vor”) and Beneš (1972) treated it as the 
<typeStatus box="[985,1087,1528,1554]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">holotype</typeStatus>
. However, 
<bibRefCitation author="Eversmann, E." box="[1211,1436,1528,1554]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="3 - 68" refId="ref73264" refString="Eversmann, E. (1847) Fauna hymenopterologica volgo-uralensis exhibens Hymenopterorum species quas in provinciis Volgam fluvium inter et montes Uralenses sitis observavit et nunc descripsit. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 20, 3 - 68." type="journal article" year="1847">Eversmann’s (1847)</bibRefCitation>
type material should be a 
<typeStatus box="[451,541,1565,1591]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">syntype</typeStatus>
, because he did not mention the number of specimens he had for description. We hereby designate the specimen in 
<collectionCode box="[582,639,1600,1626]" country="Russia" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/vmfx-g997" name="Zoological Institute, Russian Academy of Sciences" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">ZISP</collectionCode>
as the 
<typeStatus box="[721,827,1600,1626]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The head of the 
<typeStatus box="[1026,1129,1600,1626]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">lectotype</typeStatus>
is missing. The abdominal segments 1–5 are yellow (Eversmann started counting the abdominal segments with 2, accordingly he wrote “segmentis 2–6 fulvis” in the original description). The 
<typeStatus box="[732,835,1672,1698]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">lectotype</typeStatus>
is labelled as follows: “Spask Jun”, “hilaris.”, “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ev" authorityName="Ev" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">Pamphilius hilaris Ev</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[346,367,1709,1735]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
Gussakovskij det.”, “село Спасское Оренбургской губ.” (= village Spasskoe, 
<collectingRegion box="[1250,1432,1708,1734]" country="Russia" name="Orenburg" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">oblast Orenburg</collectingRegion>
, 
<geoCoordinate box="[151,260,1744,1771]" degrees="52.017" direction="north" orientation="latitude" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" precision="55" value="52.017">52.017°N</geoCoordinate>
<geoCoordinate box="[267,377,1744,1771]" degrees="56.567" direction="east" orientation="longitude" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" precision="55" value="56.567">56.567°E</geoCoordinate>
), “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Ev." authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1847" box="[406,587,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Lyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">Lyda hilaris Ev.</taxonomicName>
к. Эверсмана”, golden circle, “ 
<typeStatus box="[948,1042,1744,1770]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Syntype</typeStatus>
<taxonomicName authority="Eversmann 1847" authorityName="Eversmann" authorityYear="1847" box="[1050,1380,1744,1771]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Lyda" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hilaris">
Lyda hilaris 
<bibRefCitation author="Eversmann, E." box="[1191,1380,1744,1771]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="3 - 68" refId="ref73264" refString="Eversmann, E. (1847) Fauna hymenopterologica volgo-uralensis exhibens Hymenopterorum species quas in provinciis Volgam fluvium inter et montes Uralenses sitis observavit et nunc descripsit. Bulletin de la Societe Imperiale des Naturalistes de Moscou, 20, 3 - 68." type="journal article" year="1847">Eversmann 1847</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
vide A. Taeger 2014”, “DEI-GISHym 30352” (see https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.11405190).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1437,1492,2023]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,431,1816,1842]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Material examined.</emphasis>
About 
<specimenCount box="[513,680,1816,1842]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" type="generic">210 specimens</specimenCount>
, including the 
<typeStatus box="[841,947,1816,1842]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">lectotype</typeStatus>
. Ten specimens are known from the Russian Far East and Korea (
